      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into discs</p><p>Add the <strong>potato</strong> <strong>discs</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
